      "comment": "TREACHEROUS DAN (5) hasn't raced since last April when he kicked off his career with a second in a Nutrien Equine Classic heat before drawing wide in the final in his only other appearance. Likely to have developed with maturity and will be ready to go off two trials, winning the latest. Hails from a top yard and looks well placed for a winning return. SWEETHEART DIOR (1) is improving with racing and was good last start when runner-up at Melton, beaten a head. Likely to get the favours from this nice draw so should play a role. EL LAZZAR (6) has been freshened since drawing poorly and finishing midfield on debut but has won a trial in that time so look for improvement. TRICODE (8) draws for a trail and will be cherry-ripe after three runs back from a spell, the latest effort a fourth at Melton a week ago.",
